  <abstract>This booklet introduces the reader to the Fair Housing Amendment Act of 1988, passed by Congress making it unlawful to discriminate against families with children and people with disabilities. The law was a strong response to reports across the country that families with children are very often victims of housing discfrimination. The booklet introduces the reader to the new law and helps the reader determine if he or she has been unfairly denied housing because of their children.</abstract>
